reviewText: Given not many (or none) workout DVD that focus only on the chest, I gave this DVD a try. The exercise they offered is so basic and general that you can find them online or in a beauty magazine. The quality of the DVD is grainy, I would have returned it and ask for a refund if I were living in the US at the time but I didn't want to waste my money on shipping.
When I received the DVD it looked as if someone made a copy of the cover. Basically it is a bootleg copy. Not an Authentic DVD at all!
I really like it. It's very old school but I can feel it working. I think I just made a great investment
